Premier Sihle Zikalala has confirmed patient zero has recovered.Courtesy #DStv403 KWAZULU-NATAL - The first South African infected with the coronavirus, has recovered. READ: Coronavirus: ZCC cancels all Moria events until further notice Premier Sihle Zikalala confirmed the KwaZulu-Natal patient's recovery at a media briefing on Wednesday. "Both he and his wife are recovering. They are now in a waiting period. They will be discharged back into their family and home." The number of confirmed cases of the Covid-19 coronavirus in the country has risen to 116. There has also been an increase in local transmissions. READ: SA citizens repatriated from Wuhan test negative for COVID-19 Most of the new cases come from Gauteng, with 16 people testing positive. Meanwehile, the Health Department says citizens repatriated from Wuhan were tested and all results have come back negative. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.